00:54:07.840 --> 00:54:10.720
We're going to talk about
those three principles,

00:54:10.720 --> 00:54:14.350
but only in the last
lecture oddly enough.

00:54:14.350 --> 00:54:15.700
We're going to use them.

00:54:15.700 --> 00:54:17.650
We're going to use
these principles,

00:54:17.650 --> 00:54:20.160
but in the last
lecture I'm going

00:54:20.160 --> 00:54:24.090
to question all of the framework
that I've developed for you,

00:54:24.090 --> 00:54:26.400
and show you where
the holes are.

00:54:26.400 --> 00:54:28.140
For the first 13
weeks, I'm going

00:54:28.140 --> 00:54:32.880
to need you to willingly suspend
your disbelief as we describe

00:54:32.880 --> 00:54:39.390
the relatively straightforward
and standardized framework

00:54:39.390 --> 00:54:41.770
