01:03:53.230 --> 01:03:54.160
You're all adults.

01:03:54.160 --> 01:03:55.900
I realize that.

01:03:55.900 --> 01:03:57.760
But nevertheless, this
is a necessary part

01:03:57.760 --> 01:03:58.510
of the curriculum.

01:03:58.510 --> 01:04:02.590
So that's how we're going
to be assigning grades.

01:04:02.590 --> 01:04:05.457
In the last four
minutes, and I think

01:04:05.457 --> 01:04:07.790
I'm going to try to keep on
time for the entire semester

01:04:07.790 --> 01:04:11.510
so we end at five
before the half hour,

01:04:11.510 --> 01:04:13.420
and we start five
after the hour.

01:04:13.420 --> 01:04:16.330
In the last four minutes,
I want to tell you

01:04:16.330 --> 01:04:19.270
a little bit about how to get
the most out of this course.

01:04:19.270 --> 01:04:22.330
And we can take this up next
time if you've got questions,

01:04:22.330 --> 01:04:25.700
but I want you to spend
time thinking about this.

01:04:25.700 --> 01:04:28.960
Most of this course will
be devoted to theory.

01:04:28.960 --> 01:04:31.450
But finance is not a
theoretical subject

01:04:31.450 --> 01:04:34.060
unlike algebraic topology.

01:04:34.060 --> 01:04:35.980
That's a theoretical subject.

01:04:35.980 --> 01:04:39.610
I've never heard anybody
become a practical or applied

01:04:39.610 --> 01:04:41.530
algebraic topologist.

01:04:41.530 --> 01:04:43.990
Finance on the
other hand, there's

01:04:43.990 --> 01:04:46.540
no finance without practice.

01:04:46.540 --> 01:04:49.870
So while the course will
be focused on the theory,

01:04:49.870 --> 01:04:52.917
I need you to think about
the practical elements of it,

01:04:52.917 --> 01:04:55.250
and I'm going to help you in
a couple of different ways.

01:04:55.250 --> 01:04:57.130
One is by problems,
but the other

01:04:57.130 --> 01:05:00.670
is to encourage you to sit
in on a pro-seminar called

01:05:00.670 --> 01:05:02.882
the Practice of Finance.

01:05:02.882 --> 01:05:04.840
This is a new pro-seminar
that we're launching.

01:05:04.840 --> 01:05:07.160
September 17 is
the first meeting.

01:05:07.160 --> 01:05:09.687
It doesn't carry any units,
so you can come and go

01:05:09.687 --> 01:05:10.270
as you please.

01:05:10.270 --> 01:05:12.670
But it'll give you a sense
of the practical aspects

01:05:12.670 --> 01:05:15.340
of the industry, and in
particular information

01:05:15.340 --> 01:05:17.170
about the career
aspects of the industry

01:05:17.170 --> 01:05:20.380
like what are starting salaries
for financial analysts.

01:05:20.380 --> 01:05:22.330
Or how do I get a job
in finance if I don't

01:05:22.330 --> 01:05:23.646
have any background in it.

01:05:23.646 --> 01:05:25.270
It'll go through
those kinds of issues.

01:05:25.270 --> 01:05:28.370
So I'd encourage you
to keep that in mind.

01:05:28.370 --> 01:05:31.870
The second thing is with
respect to the course,

01:05:31.870 --> 01:05:34.840
I will give you lecture
notes ahead of time

01:05:34.840 --> 01:05:36.670
for all of the lectures.

01:05:36.670 --> 01:05:38.980
I expect you to take a
look at them in advance.

01:05:38.980 --> 01:05:39.790
Just skim them.

01:05:39.790 --> 01:05:41.290
You don't have to
read them, and try

01:05:41.290 --> 01:05:42.580
to sort out what I'm saying.

01:05:42.580 --> 01:05:44.560
But I want you to
skim it at least.

01:05:44.560 --> 01:05:47.230
And then in class I urge
you to take lots of notes,

01:05:47.230 --> 01:05:50.410
because the lecture notes
are not meant to be complete.

01:05:50.410 --> 01:05:54.070
In fact, they are
purposefully incomplete

01:05:54.070 --> 01:05:55.890
so that you have
to use your hand

01:05:55.890 --> 01:05:58.570
and write down your
impressions of the material

01:05:58.570 --> 01:05:59.920
as I'm speaking.

01:05:59.920 --> 01:06:02.470
Because in that method,
you will actually

01:06:02.470 --> 01:06:07.450
absorb more of the material,
and it'll stay with you longer.

01:06:07.450 --> 01:06:09.670
I would urge you to review
the lectures afterwards.

01:06:09.670 --> 01:06:10.776
Review what I said.

01:06:10.776 --> 01:06:12.400
Because you may have
heard what I said,

01:06:12.400 --> 01:06:14.710
but you may not have
understood what I said,

01:06:14.710 --> 01:06:17.020
and you may not be able
to apply what I said.

01:06:17.020 --> 01:06:21.350
So you need to spend time
afterwards soaking it in.

01:06:21.350 --> 01:06:22.940
I urge you to work
on the assignments

01:06:22.940 --> 01:06:24.950
in groups, but also alone.

01:06:24.950 --> 01:06:26.970
Because when you do the
midterm and final exams,

01:06:26.970 --> 01:06:28.610
you'll be doing them alone.

01:06:28.610 --> 01:06:29.780
So do both.

01:06:29.780 --> 01:06:33.080
Don't just assume that you
can do the same in groups

01:06:33.080 --> 01:06:35.240
what you will do alone.

01:06:35.240 --> 01:06:38.732
And finally, I would ask you
to ask plenty of questions.

01:06:38.732 --> 01:06:40.440
I'm going to manage
the class discussion.

01:06:40.440 --> 01:06:43.670
So that if we have time, I'd be
happy to talk about issues that

01:06:43.670 --> 01:06:46.550
are current and on your mind.

01:06:46.550 --> 01:06:50.330
Even whether or not you should
refinance your auto loan.

01:06:50.330 --> 01:06:52.520
We're happy to take those
kind of questions assuming

01:06:52.520 --> 01:06:55.220
that it's apropos, and
that we have the time

01:06:55.220 --> 01:06:56.720
to be able to cover that.

01:06:56.720 --> 01:06:57.950
I want you to get engaged.

01:06:57.950 --> 01:06:59.780
I want you to take
this course personally,

01:06:59.780 --> 01:07:01.446
because that's the
only way you're going

01:07:01.446 --> 01:07:03.239
to really learn the material.

01:07:03.239 --> 01:07:04.530
All right, thank you very much.

01:07:04.530 --> 01:07:05.280
We're out of time.

01:07:05.280 --> 01:07:07.580
We'll see you next Monday.

